    "recent_post_texts": [
      "South Korea just moved to classify crypto as long-term national wealth under a new National Asset Basic Act, covering roughly $940B in state assets. That's a government treating bitcoin and crypto like gold or land reserves, not a speculative side bet. \ud83c\uddf0\ud83c\uddf7\ud83d\udcb0",
      "Glassnode says top traders on Hyperliquid (a crypto derivatives exchange) are running very aggressive leveraged $BTC longs, above levels seen at the last run to $83K. Crowded leverage cuts both ways: fuels rallies, but also feeds liquidation cascades. \ud83c\udfa2\u26a0\ufe0f",
      "DeFi (decentralized finance, crypto lending/trading without a middleman) just took another hit: Ostium, a derivatives platform, lost $18M to an oracle exploit. Oracles feed price data on-chain -- manipulate the feed, and you can drain the protocol without tou\u2026",
      "JUST IN: PYPL just surged over 17% while most of crypto and megacap tech is only up modestly. That's a massive single-day move for a company this size -- usually means a real earnings or business update, not just market drift. Worth watching what's driving it\u2026",
      "Crypto is red across the board today: BTC down 2%, ETH down 3.4%, SOL down 3.2%. Meanwhile Bitwise data shows crypto-linked stocks (COIN, MSTR, miners) actually returned 23% in H1 2026, beating nearly every asset class even as crypto prices themselves fell 36\u2026",
      "Miners and HOOD getting hit hard today: MARA -6.4%, RIOT -7.8%, HOOD -6.2%, even as BTC itself is down a modest 0.9%. When crypto-adjacent stocks fall much harder than the coin they're tied to, it usually means leverage/sentiment unwinding faster than the und\u2026",
      "Visa just launched a platform (VSP) letting banks and fintechs offer stablecoin services -- reaching over 200 million merchants worldwide. This isn't Visa issuing its own coin; it's Visa becoming the plumbing that lets any bank plug into stablecoins without b\u2026",
      "\ud83d\udea8 JUST IN: broad red day across risk assets. BTC -1.3% near $64K, ETH -2.7%, but the real damage is in crypto-adjacent stocks: HOOD -8.2%, MARA -7%, RIOT -6.4%, COIN -4%, MSTR -3.5%. Tech also weak (AMD -5.3%, ORCL -6.2\u2026",
      "\ud83d\udcb0 Citadel Securities, one of the biggest market makers on Wall Street, just put $400M into Crypto.com, valuing the exchange at $20B. Traditional finance heavyweights keep buying into crypto infrastructure even while pri\u2026",
      "\ud83d\udcca DTCC -- the clearinghouse that settles nearly every US stock trade -- just moved tokenized securities from pilot testing into live, real trading. Meanwhile Cantor and Securitize are separately working on blockchain-based IPOs."
    ],
